qudt_table: reference table of QUDT units in english (US)

qudt_table_en_us.Rd

qudt_table contains units-of-measure details outlined by the Quantities, Units, Dimensions and dataTypes organization [QUDT.org](https://qudt.org/). The table provides a resource for documenting units of type QUDT in EML metadata. This is a subset of the qudt_table that features only english (US) language entries.

Usage

qudt_table_en_us

Format

A dataframe; rows will vary as QUDT adds units and columns may vary if the query is altered.

unit

unit URI

label

short description of the unit

hasDimensionVector

dimension vector of unit

conversionMultiplier

multiplier to SI

lang

language format (US or British english)

name

unit identifier

Source

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/qudt/qudt-public-repo/master/vocab/unit/VOCAB_QUDT-UNITS-ALL-v2.1.ttl

Note

The unit description currently is commented out in the query owing to poorly formatted text and character issues. This is not needed in the current capeml workflow.

Even when description is included in the query, be cautious of filtering by datatype (e.g., Latex) as even though description is included as an optional return the filter will omit entries without a datatype.

ucumCode currently is commented out in the query as including this variable results in many duplicate entries that vary only by the ucumCode value. ucumCode is not part of the capeml workflow; consider aggregating these values into an array if needed in the future.

Return is restricted to entries noted as being documented in english (US).
